betterquesting.name: Crucible (The Basics)
betterquesting.desc: You have already made at least one crucible in this pack before, so you should be able to complete this quest very easily. However, this quest will take that crucible away from you!

betterquesting.name: Notch Apple (The Basics)
betterquesting.desc: You should've already made a notch apple (enchanted golden apple) but this quest will take it away when you claim your reward.

betterquesting.name: Casts
betterquesting.desc: You should have already been requested to make all of the Tinkers' Casts, or maybe not. They don't even unlock anything (other than completing this quest) but you now need to make all of them to unlock the rest of the quests in the BQ questbook.

betterquesting.name: Power Bank (Industrial Revolution)
betterquesting.desc: You've made this, probably multible times before. All I ask is you give up a bit of your power storage to me, thank you for your donation.

betterquesting.name: Vibrant Capacitor Bank (Industrial Revolution)
betterquesting.desc: You've made this before. Stop looking at the description.... please.

betterquesting.name: Cobblestone Framework (Industrial Revolution)
betterquesting.desc: You should have one of these laying around in some chest somewhere, I bet you haven't even used it since I told you to make it, how sad.

betterquesting.name: Weather Obelisk
betterquesting.desc: You might still have this outside your base. Do you still remember what rain looks like? If you answered no, go look outside. If you do know what rain looks like, start looking in some chests.

betterquesting.name: Painting Machine (Industrial Revolution)
betterquesting.desc: I can say with great assurance that you have never used this machine in your life. Let me take it off your hands.

betterquesting.name: Fluid Conduit (Industrial Revolution)
betterquesting.desc: As appose to grabbing some fluid conduits from your walls/factory, you can always just make 10 more.

betterquesting.name: Fortune Upgrade (Industrial Revolution)
betterquesting.desc: Yes, the sieve upgrade. I'm sure you haven't thought about that in like a year.

betterquesting.name: Killer Joe (Industrial Revolution)
betterquesting.desc: Check your mob spawner. Then again, you probably considered this machine obsolete at this point.

betterquesting.name: Aversion Obelisk (Industrial Revolution)
betterquesting.desc: I don't know why you would have used this or where you would have put it, good luck!

betterquesting.name: Enchantment Table (The Basics)
betterquesting.desc: You have already been instructed to make an enchantment table in The Basics questline, so you should have at least one laying around. However, what I haven't told you yet is that I am going to be taking your enchantment table away from you! Sorry!

betterquesting.name: Experiance Obelisk (Industrial Revolution)
betterquesting.desc: Please give me your XP storage, thank you!

betterquesting.name: Nullifier (Industrial Revolution)
betterquesting.desc: I forget what this does, I bet you do to.

betterquesting.name: Crusher (Industrial Revolution)
betterquesting.desc: Now I bet you use this machine on the daily, no joke. So it might be worthh it just to make the parts again so you don't loose your multiblock

betterquesting.name: Nether Star Generator x64 (Industrial Revolution)
betterquesting.desc: This might take you a while to get, especially for me just to take it away again..... oh well! Sucks to be you!

betterquesting.name: Lazuli Transport Pipe (Pipes & Power Plus)
betterquesting.desc: I bet you never used this pipe, all it does is paint items.

betterquesting.name: Cryo-Stabalized Fluxduct (Pipes & Power Plus)
betterquesting.desc: These very well could be powering your base right now! Then again, EnderIO conduits are a thing.

betterquesting.name: Void Fluid Pipes (Pipes & Power Plus)
betterquesting.desc: Somewhat useful. However you may have only built one. You might want to make another one.

betterquesting.name: Crafting Logistics Pipe Mk3 (Pipes & Power Plus)
betterquesting.desc: You have either used this pipe to death every since you made it & it has been very very useful to you, or you stuck it in a chest or trashcan somewhere and never thought about it again.... UNTIL TODAY!

betterquesting.name: Advanced Photovalic Cell (Pipes & Power Plus)
betterquesting.desc: EnderIO's attempt at solar panels. These are the upgraded kind.

betterquesting.name: Kinetic Dyanmo (Pipes & Power Plus)
betterquesting.desc: It's a kinetic dynamo what do you want me to say?

betterquesting.name: Reactent Dynamo (Pipes & Power Plus)
betterquesting.desc: Generates power.... I think. Remember you can always look in the old and outdated HQM book for more info on these. Jog your memory maybe?

betterquesting.name: HV Transformer (Pipes & Powe Plus)
betterquesting.desc: Is anyone even reading these descriptions?

betterquesting.name: Adventure Backpack (Storage)
betterquesting.desc: I think you did one of three things with this item. 1) You made it and stuck it in a chest somewhere never to be seen again. 2) You are currently using it to store a bunch of useful items and are dreading the idea of submiting it to me. 3) You made the backpack, equiped it, and forgot about its existence.

betterquesting.name: Framed Drawer (Storage)
betterquesting.desc: It might seem like a random item to hand in to varify that you have completed all of the storage questline, but, it is possible to not have done the framed drawer quest in HQM, but complete every other quest in storage. That is the goal of this questline btw, in case you still weren't getting it.

betterquesting.name: Resonant Strongbox (Storage)
betterquesting.desc: This is probably sitting in a chest somewhere, you should have better ways of storing things by now.

betterquesting.name: Iron Backpack Upgrades (Storage)
betterquesting.desc: Remember that dreadful time in your life when you had to create all of the iron backpack upgrades? That was fun right!?

betterquesting.name: Backpack Tank
betterquesting.desc: If you have already applied your tank to your adventure backpack, you might need to make a new one. Or maybe not.... do you really think I know how any of these mods work!? I just run through NEI or JEI or whatever I put in this modpack and say "Oh, that looks like a good item for a quest!" I don't actually do any research or put any thought into this jeeze! How do you think I've managed to surpass 800 quests!?

betterquesting.name: Slightly Larger Chest (Storage)
betterquesting.desc: A slightly larger chest, what do you want me to say?

betterquesting.name: Wireless Booster (Storage)
betterquesting.desc: Honestly, looking back at the quests regarding AE2, I did really poorly. I didn't even have you make a wireless terminal, which is required for the wireless booster to be in any way useful! Sorry about that. Anyway, give me the wireless booster.

betterquesting.name: Nitor Wart Seeds (Farming with Agricraft)
betterquesting.desc: Seeds are pretty easy to get once you have the crop, so you must turn in 32 Nitro Wart Seeds. Remember to crossbreed to get better strength, gain, and growth.§2

betterquesting.name: Plombean Seeds (Farming With Agricraft)
betterquesting.desc: Seeds are pretty easy to get once you have the crop, so you must turn in 32 Plombean Seeds. Remember to crossbreed to get better strength, gain, and growth.

betterquesting.name: Platiolus Seeds (Farming With Agricraft)
betterquesting.desc: Seeds are pretty easy to get once you have the crop, so you must turn in 32 Platiolus Seeds. Remember to crossbreed to get better strength, gain, and growth.

betterquesting.name: Jaslumine Seeds (Farming With Agricraft)
betterquesting.desc: Seeds are pretty easy to get once you have the crop, so you must turn in 32 Jaslumine Seeds. Remember to crossbreed to get better strength, gain, and growth.

betterquesting.name: Emeryllis Seeds (Farming With Agricraft)
betterquesting.desc: Seeds are pretty easy to get once you have the crop, so you must turn in 32 Emeryllis Seeds. Remember to crossbreed to get better strength, gain, and growth.

betterquesting.name: Cactus Seeds (Farming With Agricraft)
betterquesting.desc: Seeds are pretty easy to get once you have the crop, so you must turn in 32 Cactus Seeds. Remember to crossbreed to get better strength, gain, and growth.

betterquesting.name: Pink Tulip Seeds (Farming With Agricraft)
betterquesting.desc: Seeds are pretty easy to get once you have the crop, so you must turn in 32 Pink Tulip Seeds. Remember to crossbreed to get better strength, gain, and growth.

betterquesting.name: White Mushroom Spore (Farming With Pam)
betterquesting.desc: You've gathered this before I swear.

betterquesting.name: Juices (Farming With Pam)
betterquesting.desc: 1 of every juice from Pam's Harvestcraft. They are all unfulfilling snacks, so this is pretty much just a waste of time.

betterquesting.name: Pomegranit Smoothie (Farming With Pam)
betterquesting.desc: The last smoothie quest in the Pam's questline in the HQM book.

betterquesting.name: Jelly Sandwiches
betterquesting.desc: A quest for all 24 jelly sandwiches in Pam's. Also in the HQM book.

betterquesting.name: Sweet Potato (Dining With Pam)
betterquesting.desc: In HQM, this quest is unlocked by 100% completing Cooking With Pam. This quest is here to verify that you have completed Cooking With Pam

betterquesting.name: Jewled Apple (Dining With Pam)
betterquesting.desc: A stand alone quest in Dining With Pam.

betterquesting.name: Blackberry Yogurt (Dining With Pam)
betterquesting.desc: The last yogurt you have to make in Dining With Pam

betterquesting.name: Random Taco (Dining With Pam)
betterquesting.desc: Unlocked in Dining With Pam by completing 8 other quests in the questline.

betterquesting.name: Jelly (Dining With Pam)
betterquesting.desc: A quest for all 25 jellies in Pam's. Also a quest in HQM. Does not unlock anything else in the HQM book.

betterquesting.name: Gooseberry Sappling
betterquesting.desc: The last sappling you have to gather from Pam's in HQM.

betterquesting.name: Brownie (Dining With Pam)
betterquesting.desc: The last desert quest in HQM.

betterquesting.name: Beef Wellington (Dining With Pam)
betterquesting.desc: Requires many other food quests to be completed in HQM.

betterquesting.name: Breeder (Farming With Tech)
betterquesting.desc: The last MFR machine in HQM.

betterquesting.name: Upgrade (Emerald) (Farming With Tech)
betterquesting.desc: The last MFR upgrade in HQM.

betterquesting.name: Unstable Tools (Extra Random)
betterquesting.desc: A quest for all the tools/weapons made with Stable/Unstable Ingots. Also a quest in HQM.

betterquesting.name: Block Update Detectors (Extra Random)
betterquesting.desc: (Block Update Detector & Advanced Block Update Detector) A stand-a-lone quest in HQM.

betterquesting.name: Energy Trashcan (Extra Random)
betterquesting.desc: The last trashcan quest in HQM.

betterquesting.name: Reinforced Dark Glass (Extra Random)
betterquesting.desc: The end of a quest section in HQM.

betterquesting.name: Inverted Dark Ethereal Glass
betterquesting.desc: The end of a quest section in HQM.

betterquesting.name: Ender Quarry (Extra Random)
betterquesting.desc: The end of a quest section in HQM.

betterquesting.name: Traveler's Goggles (Transportation)
betterquesting.desc: Part of the tinkers' construct traveling gear. Also a quest in HQM

betterquesting.name: Elevator (Transportation)
betterquesting.desc: Allows you to travel between floors easily. Two are required. Also a quest in HQM

betterquesting.name: Staff of Traveling + Travel Anchors (Transportation)
betterquesting.desc: The staff of traveling lets you teleport between two or more travel anchors, or it can teleport you a short distance. Also a quest in HQM.

betterquesting.name: Armored Resonant Jetpack (Transportation)
betterquesting.desc: The final armored jetpack in the Simply Jetpacks mod. 20 million RF to fully fuel. Uses 450 RF a tick. Gives 4 points of armor. Also a quest in HQM.

betterquesting.name: Glider Wings (Transportation)
betterquesting.desc: Ender IO's take on a glider. Also a quest in HQM.

betterquesting.name: Nether Coal Ore (Exploration)
betterquesting.desc: Coal Ore found in the nether. Also a quest in HQM

betterquesting.name: Nether Emerald Ore (Exploration)
betterquesting.desc: Emerald Ore found in the nether. Also a quest in HQM.

betterquesting.name: Nether Uranium Ore. (Exploration)
betterquesting.desc: Uranium Ore found in the nether. Also a quest in HQM.

betterquesting.name: Portal to the Last Millenium
betterquesting.desc: A portal to a skyblock-like dimension. Also a quest in HQM.

betterquesting.name: Ultimate Oxygen Decompressor
betterquesting.desc: Fills air tanks with oxygen the fastest. Also a quest in HQM.

betterquesting.name: Ultimate Oxygen Compressor
betterquesting.desc: The best Oxygen Compressor. Also a quest in HQM.

betterquesting.name: Advanced Refinery
betterquesting.desc: Faster than a regular refinery. Also holds more fuel. Also a quest in HQM.

betterquesting.name: Ultimate Fuel Loader
betterquesting.desc: Loads fuel the fastest and has the most capacity. Also a quest in HQM.

betterquesting.name: Tier 9 Rocket Workbench Schematic (Galactic Exploration)
betterquesting.desc: The last NASA Schematic you are obligated to collect. You are allowed to keep this one. They're really really hard to find.

betterquesting.name: Destination Analyzer
betterquesting.desc: The final quest. After you complete this quest, if you have completed all other quests in the PART 2 questline, I know you have fully 100% completed the HQM book. All 800 quests! And to that, I must congratulate you. That questbook is hard. Really. Really. Really. Really hard. Recipe changes roadblocked you, there may have been some times where you felt like quitting this modpack. Some people may have, but you haven't. You perpervered. I am extremely proud of you. I know how long the HQM book took you to complete. It probably took you longer than the year I spent making it. Again congratulations!                  Oh.... you think it's over? You can finally delete this modpack for good and never lay eyes on it again!? HAHAH, yeah right!! The HQM book was only the begining. Welcome to PART TWO, OF QUESTING MAYHEM! It will be harder, grinder, more challenging, more insane, did I mention harder? Once you have completed the "PART 2" Questline fully, another questline will unlock. Let's go!

betterquesting.name: Lexica Botania
betterquesting.desc: The Lexica Botania book has all of the info you need for Botania.

betterquesting.name: Magical Petals
betterquesting.desc: You can find flowers from Botania growing on the ground. Collect them and turn them into mystical petals. There should be 16.

betterquesting.name: Mana Wand
betterquesting.desc: Craft a wand of the forest. The colors are determined by the color of the petals you used to craft the wand. This wand is very important when dealing with mana. Use your lexica botanica for more info.

betterquesting.name: Apothecary
betterquesting.desc: A magical block that is used to craft flowers and other useful magical items. Make sure to fill the apothecary with water. To craft, simply throw in the required items.

betterquesting.name: Mana Manipulation
betterquesting.desc: Use the mana pool to turn items into other items. Each craft requires a specific amount of mana in the mana pool.

betterquesting.name: Pure Daisy
betterquesting.desc: The pure daisy is an important and powerful flower in botania. Use it to make livingwood and livingrock, common ingredients for crafting.

betterquesting.name: Mana Spreading
betterquesting.desc: Use mana spreaders to transport and distribute mana. You can use your wand of the forest to link your mana spreaders to mana producers like Nightshades. You can also use your wand of the forest to have the mana "spread" to a mana consumer like a mana pool. Remember, the mana must always go through a mana spreader, you can't have mana go from a Nightshade to a Mana Pool. It has to go from the Nightshade, to the Mana Spreader, to the Mana Pool. Use your lexica botania for more info.

betterquesting.name: Nightshades
betterquesting.desc: Generates mana passivly during night. Will decay after 3 days. Use your lexica botania for more info.

betterquesting.name: Hydrogeas
betterquesting.desc: Generates mana passivly through nearby water sources. Will decay in 3 days. Use your lexica botania for more info.

betterquesting.name: Gourmaryllis
betterquesting.desc: Produces mana through edibles on the floor.

betterquesting.name: Spectrolus
betterquesting.desc: Produces mana by eating colored wool.

betterquesting.name: Endoflames
betterquesting.desc: Generates mana by burning vanilla fuels. Simply drop a burnable vanilla item near the endoflame and it will produce a bit of mana. Use your lexica botania for more info.

betterquesting.name: Dayblooms
betterquesting.desc: Generates mana passivly through sunlight. Will decay after 3 days. Use your lexica botania for more info.

betterquesting.name: Thermalily
betterquesting.desc: Thermalilies produce mana by eating lava source blocks. One source block of lava will fill up their entire internal buffer, so transport the mana fast! Use your lexica botania for more info.

betterquesting.name: Rosa Arcana
betterquesting.desc: Produces mana by taking nearby player's XP.

betterquesting.name: Munchdew
betterquesting.desc: Generates mana by eating nearby leaf blocks.

betterquesting.name: Rafflowsia
betterquesting.desc: Produces mana by eating dayblooms, nightshades, and hydroangeas

betterquesting.name: Narslimmus
betterquesting.desc: Produces mana through nearby slime entities

betterquesting.name: Mana Items
betterquesting.desc: You can transform some vanilla items into mana-infused varients. Simply drop the base item into the mana pool, and you will have a mana version.

betterquesting.name: Runic Altar
betterquesting.desc: The runic altar is used to craft many items in Botania. Similar to the mana pool, drop the required items on to the altar. Make sure the altar has mana by pointing a mana spreader at it. You will know when you have the recipe correct. When the recipe is correct, drop a piece of livingrock onto the alter.

betterquesting.name: Elemental Runes
betterquesting.desc: Runes are crafted on the Runic Altar. Among many more, there is a Water Rune, a Fire Rune, an Earth Rune, and an Air Rune.

betterquesting.name: Seasonal Runes
betterquesting.desc: There are Runes for every season; Winter, Spring, Summer, and Autumn. The recipes for these runes include some elemental runes.

betterquesting.name: Complex Runes
betterquesting.desc: The final runes have somewhat more complex recipes.

betterquesting.name: Terra Firma Rod
betterquesting.desc: Flatens land by adding or removing dirt to/from the area. Uses a bit of mana per use.

betterquesting.name: The Manatide Bellows
betterquesting.desc: Place this block next to a mana pool or furnace. It will increase the mana output rate of mana pools. If you place it next to a furnace, it will increase the rate and efficiency of the furnace.

betterquesting.name: Snowflake Pendant
betterquesting.desc: When worn as a bauble, it turns water source blocks into ice. The ice will only last while the player is in the area.

betterquesting.name: Ring of Chordata
betterquesting.desc: When worn as a bauble, you will swim faster, walk underwater faster, and see underwater better.

betterquesting.name: Soujourner's Sash
betterquesting.desc: When worn as a bauble, you will be able to run faster, jump higher, and fall from greater heights. You will also have step-assist.

betterquesting.name: Land Rod
betterquesting.desc: Creates dirt on right-click. Requires a bit of mana per use.

betterquesting.name: Seas Rod
betterquesting.desc: Creates water on right-click. Uses a bit of mana per use.

betterquesting.name: Sky Rod
betterquesting.desc: Throws the player 35 blocks in the air on right-click. Uses a bit of mana per use.

betterquesting.name: Hell Rod
betterquesting.desc: Will produce a ring of fire around the player. Uses some mana per use.

betterquesting.name: Molten Core Rod
betterquesting.desc: Smelts blocks on right click. The rod will only smelt blocks and the blocks must be able to smelt into another block. For example, if you try to use the rod on gold ore, the gold ore will stay gold ore and not turn into a gold ingot. However, if you use the rod on cobblestone, the cobblestone will turn into smooth stone. Uses a bit of mana per use.

betterquesting.name: Depth Rod
betterquesting.desc: Similar to the Rod of the Lands. Will create cobblestone on right-click. Uses a bit of mana per use.

betterquesting.name: Highlands Rod
betterquesting.desc: Similar to the Rod of the Lands. However, this rod can place dirt in mid-air.

betterquesting.name: Terrestrial Agglomeration Plate
betterquesting.desc: Crafting Terrestrial Agglomeration Plates is the first step in creating terrasteel. Place one Terrestrial Agglomeration Plate in the middle of a lapis and livingrock checkerboard. See the setup in your Lexica Botania, you can also click "visulize" for more help.

betterquesting.name: Sparks
betterquesting.desc: The Terrestrial Agglomeration Plate requires mana. The most efficient method of getting mana to the plate, accourding to the book, are sparks. Use your lexica botania for more info.

betterquesting.name: Terrasteel
betterquesting.desc: Throwing 1 manasteel, 1 manaperal, and 1 mana diamond on the Terrestrial Agglomeration Plate will start the ritual for terrasteel. Remember, if you pick up any of the items, the ritual will cancel. The ritual also requires half a mana pool. Using multiple sparks are recomended.

betterquesting.name: Block of Terrasteel
betterquesting.desc: Like all other metal blocks in Minecraft, 9 ingots are required to make one block. Oh, you think this is hard... heh-he. ;)

betterquesting.name: Terrasteel x64
betterquesting.desc: You read it correctly. Just be thankful I didn't say "Terrasteel Block x64"

betterquesting.name: Terrasteel Armour
betterquesting.desc: The Terrasteel Armour Set takes available mana when you are hit so the armour decays slower. It also has diamond armour-like properties.

betterquesting.name: Elven Crafting
betterquesting.desc: Some misc items you can craft with elven items. To learn more about each individual item, search them in your lexica botania OR see the recipe for an item and click the right arrow at the top!

betterquesting.name: Alfheim
betterquesting.desc: Alfheim is a dimension of mystical elves. You can create a portal to alfheim, but it will not be strong enough for you to visit in person. However, you can throw items through the portal and the elves may give you something in return. The portal requires 8 livingwood, 3 glimmering livingwood, 1 elven gateway core, 2 manapools, and 2 pylons. Read your lexica botania for more info and to view the setup. After you create the portal, it is recomended you throw your lexica botania book through the portal to gain extra knowledge.

betterquesting.name: Elven Items
betterquesting.desc: Throw 2 manasteel through the portal to get 1 elementium. Throw living wood through the portal to get dreamwood. Throw mana pearls through to get pixie dust. Throw mana diamond through to get dragonstone. Throw managlass through to get Alfglass.

betterquesting.name: Drums
betterquesting.desc: There are 3 drums in Botania. The drum of the wild harvests tall grass, flowers, and crops in a 25x25x7 area when supplied with a mana burst. The drum of the canopy harvests leaves in a 24 block diameter and 7 block height. Leaves drop items as if a hand broke them. The drum of gathering shears nearby sheep. It will also fill buckets with milk if the bucket is under a cow. To give the drums mana, you must use a mana pulse spreader or mana blaster. A regular mana spreader will not work.

betterquesting.name: Bulk Trading
betterquesting.desc: You have already traded with the elves, but you might need some more items.

betterquesting.name: Bifrost Rod
betterquesting.desc: Creates magical bridges when right-clicked. Uses a bit of mana per use.

betterquesting.name: Horns
betterquesting.desc: There are 3 horns in Botania. The horn of the wild removes nearby grass and flowers from the ground. Horn of the canopy removes nearby leaves. Horn of the covering removes nearby snow from the ground.

betterquesting.name: Manasteel Tools
betterquesting.desc: Basic tools & weapons you can make with manasteel.

betterquesting.name: Terrasteel Tools
betterquesting.desc: Basic tools & weapons you can make with terrasteel. There are different ranks on the terra shatterer. These ranks do not affect this quest, you can submit any ranked terra shatterer.

betterquesting.name: Manasteel Helmet
betterquesting.desc: A helmet made out of manasteel. Gives 1 point of armour. When the entire manasteel set is worn, mana cost on tools & rods is recuded by 10%

betterquesting.name: Manasteel Chestplate
betterquesting.desc: A chestplate made out of manasteel. Gives 3 points of armour. When the entire manasteel set is worn, mana cost on tools and rods is reduced by 10 percent.

betterquesting.name: Manasteel Leggings
betterquesting.desc: Leggings made out of manasteel. Gives 2.5 points of armour. When the entire manasteel set is worn, mana cost on tools and rods is reduced by 10 percent.

betterquesting.name: Manasteel Boots
betterquesting.desc: Boots made out of manasteel. Gives 1 point of armour. When the entire manasteel set is worn, mana cost on tools and rods is reduced by 10 percent.

betterquesting.name: Terrasteel Helmet
betterquesting.desc: A helmet made out of terrasteel. Gives 1.5 points of armour. When the entire terrasteel set is worn, you will recive the will of the ancients (passive mana generation, mana cost on tools and rods will decrease by 20 percent, passive regeneration when hunger bar is not full, all wills dropped by the Guardian of Gaia ON HARD MODE)

betterquesting.name: Terrasteel Chestplate
betterquesting.desc: A chestplate made out of terrasteel. Gives 4 armour points. When the entire terrasteel set is worn, you will recive the will of the ancients (passive mana generation, mana cost on tools and rods will decrease by 20 percent, passive regeneration when hunger bar is not full, all wills dropped by the Guardian of Gaia ON HARD MODE)

betterquesting.name: Terrasteel Leggings
betterquesting.desc: Leggings made out of terrasteel. Gives 3 armour points. When the entire terrasteel set is worn, you will recive the will of the ancients (passive mana generation, mana cost on tools and rods will decrease by 20 percent, passive regeneration when hunger bar is not full, all wills dropped by the Guardian of Gaia ON HARD MODE)

betterquesting.name: Terrasteel Boots
betterquesting.desc: Boots made out of terrasteel. Gives 1.5 armour points. When the entire terrasteel set is worn, you will recive the will of the ancients (passive mana generation, mana cost on tools and rods will decrease by 20 percent, passive regeneration when hunger bar is not full, all wills dropped by the Guardian of Gaia ON HARD MODE)

betterquesting.name: Elementium Boots
betterquesting.desc: Boots made out of elementium. Gives an 11 percent chance to spawn a pixie after the player has been attacked. The pixie will go after the attacker. The chance stacks with each piece of elementium armour. When the entire elementium set is worn, the player will recieve the Great Fairy's Blessing. (decreases mana cost on tools & rods by 10 percent, pixies near the player will get a random potion effect.)

betterquesting.name: Elementium Leggings
betterquesting.desc: Leggings made out of elementium. Gives 2.5 armour points. Gives an 11 percent chance to spawn a pixie after the player has been attacked. The pixie will go after the attacker. The chance stacks with each piece of elementium armour. When the entire elementium set is worn, the player will recieve the Great Fairy's Blessing. (decreases mana cost on tools & rods by 10 percent, pixies near the player will get a random potion effect.)

betterquesting.name: Elementium Chestplate
betterquesting.desc: A chestplate made out of elementium. Gives 3 points of armour. Gives an 11 percent chance to spawn a pixie after the player has been attacked. The pixie will go after the attacker. The chance stacks with each piece of elementium armour. When the entire elementium set is worn, the player will recieve the Great Fairy's Blessing. (decreases mana cost on tools & rods by 10 percent, pixies near the player will get a random potion effect.)

betterquesting.name: Elementium Helmet
betterquesting.desc: A helmet made out of elementium. Gives 1 armour point. Gives an 11 percent chance to spawn a pixie after the player has been attacked. The pixie will go after the attacker. The chance stacks with each piece of elementium armour. When the entire elementium set is worn, the player will recieve the Great Fairy's Blessing. (decreases mana cost on tools & rods by 10 percent, pixies near the player will get a random potion effect.)

betterquesting.name: Manasteel Helmet
betterquesting.desc: A helmet made out of manasteel. Gives 1 point of armour. When the entire manasteel set is worn, mana cost on items and rods is reduced by 10 percent

betterquesting.name: Guardian Of Gaia
betterquesting.desc: The Guardian Of Gaia is a boss you can summon. To summon the Guardian Of Gaia, you must place 4 Gaia Pylons around an activated beacon and right-click the beacon with an ingot of terrasteel. The Guardian will spawn and a border will form around the pylons, making it so you can't escape. The battle is intended to be very hard, so don't do it unless you're ready. If you kill the Guardian Of Gaia, it will drop Gaia spirits which are used for several crafts as well as advancing forward in Botania.

betterquesting.name: Guardian Of Gaia (HARD MODE!)
betterquesting.desc: To summon the hard version of the Guardian of Gaia, the same setup is used, but you click the beacon with a Gaia Spirit Ingot instead of a terrasteel ingot. The hard mode of the Gaia Guardian fight is much harder than the original, hense the name. This time, the Guardian has 15 extra armour points, can teleport every 2.25 seconds in stage 2 and 1.75 seconds in stage 3, launches magic missiles, creates an extra trap in stage 3, and wither skeletons now hold elementium swords. Deffiently a lot to handle. If you manage to defeat the Guardian Of Gaia in hard mode, you will be rewarded with more gaia spirits and a dice of fate. You may even win some more items if your lucky!

betterquesting.name: Elementium Tools
betterquesting.desc: Basic tools & weapons you can make with elementium.

betterquesting.name: Mana Blaster
betterquesting.desc: Blasts mana on right click. Can be used to give blocks/flowers mana. Requires the player to have a mana tablet with some mana in it.

betterquesting.name: Band of Aura
betterquesting.desc: Slowly creats mana when in a player's inventory. All mana will go into the player's mana tablet. Mana tablet required.

betterquesting.name: Shifting Crust Rod
betterquesting.desc: Will replace blocks in a 7x7 area with another block. Shift-right-click on a block to select the block you want.

betterquesting.name: Charm of the Diva
betterquesting.desc: Will charm hostile mobs and make them attack another enemy instead of you. There must be another enemy around in order to work though.

betterquesting.name: Spectranthemum
betterquesting.desc: Teleports items to a specific location.

betterquesting.name: Tangleberrie
betterquesting.desc: Keeps mobs and animals near the flower.

betterquesting.name: Heisei Dream
betterquesting.desc: Makes nearby mobs fight each other.

betterquesting.name: Crafting with Gaia
betterquesting.desc: Misc items that you can make with Gaia Spirits. For info on all of the items, seach them up in the Lexica Botania index.

betterquesting.name: Pollidisiac
betterquesting.desc: Feeds nearby animals and makes them breed.

betterquesting.name: Solegnolia
betterquesting.desc: Makes nearby dropped items unaffected from the ring of magnetization.

betterquesting.name: Vinculotus
betterquesting.desc: Makes endermen teleport to the flower.

betterquesting.name: Rannuncarpus
betterquesting.desc: Places blocks on another specified block.

betterquesting.name: Hopperhock
betterquesting.desc: Collects narby items on the ground and places them into a nearby inventory, like a chest.

betterquesting.name: Tigerseye
betterquesting.desc: Prevents creepers from explosions. Also makes creepers run away from players.

betterquesting.name: Orechid Ignem
betterquesting.desc: Turns nearby ore into nether ores. (For example, nether quartz, nether coal ore, nether copper ore, and nether lapis ore)

betterquesting.name: Orechid
betterquesting.desc: Turns nearby stone into overworld ores. (for examample, diamond, iron, and gold ore.)

betterquesting.name: Medumone
betterquesting.desc: Gives nearby mobs a slowness debuf. Makes nearby mobs slow.

betterquesting.name: Jiyuulia
betterquesting.desc: Keeps mobs away from where ever it is placed.

betterquesting.name: Marimorphosis
betterquesting.desc: Turns nearby stone into decorative stone from Botania.

betterquesting.name: Daffomill
betterquesting.desc: Pushes dropped items in a specified direction.

betterquesting.name: Mana Tablet
betterquesting.desc: The mana tablet is a way of transporting mana. If you throw it in a mana pool, it will gather mana in its internal storage. Tools & Rods that require mana will use the mana tablet's mana before anything else.

betterquesting.name: Part Two
betterquesting.desc: Welcome! If you are reading this, you have taken your first steps to completing part one, and unlocking part two of questing mayhem. Let me explain. This questline contains quests for all of the items at the end of questlines and quest paths. Pretty much, if a quest doesn't unlock anything in the HQM book, it is also here. You must complete this questline to unlock any other questline in the Better Questing book. You might know where I am headed. Therefore, because final quests from HQM make up this questline, YOU MUST COMPLETE EVERY, SINGLE, QUEST IN THE HQM BOOK! It honestly isn't as hard as you probably think. As you go through the HQM questbook, you will also be completing this questline. There are no rewards given in this questline, so if I were you, I'd just ignore this book until you have 100 percent completed your HQM book. It is recomended that you start at the quest in the top right hand corner, and move down, vertically, the row it is in. Once you're at the bottom, go to the next row and start from the bottom. No matter which way you do it, you will still have to complete every quest in the questline and every quest in HQM. Don't worry, it's worth it.... maybe. Good luck! I'll see you in QUESTING MAYHEM PART TWO!

betterquesting.name: An Introduction To Magic
betterquesting.desc: A questline for Botania. Botania adds nature-based magic.
